Optimizes the `bin/magento media-gallery:sync` command (Magento_MediaGallerySynchronization),
which on stores with a large pub/media tree runs for a very long time and can finish without
adding any rows to media_gallery_asset.

Symptom / root cause:
FetchMediaStorageFileBatches::execute() scanned the WHOLE pub/media tree via
Filesystem::readRecursively(). readRecursively() is eager: it walks every file under pub/media,
builds a full array of relative paths and sort()s it BEFORE the generator yields its first batch.
Two consequences:
  1) Slow: the entire media tree (including the derived resize cache under catalog/product/cache/**)
     is walked and sorted up front on every run.
  2) No data imported: because nothing is yielded until the full walk+sort completes, a run that
     is interrupted or times out during the walk commits zero batches, so media_gallery_asset
     stays empty even though the command "ran".

Fix:
  * Scan only the configured media_gallery_image_folders (system/media_storage_configuration/
    allowed_resources/media_gallery_image_folders), mirroring Magento\MediaGalleryUi\Model\
    Directories\GetDirectoryTree, instead of the whole media root. The configured whitelist is the
    single source of truth for what is synchronised: every whitelisted folder is scanned in full,
    including all of its sub-directories.
  * Walk each folder LAZILY through the Filesystem abstraction (ReadInterface::read()/isDirectory()),
    yielding files as they are discovered. This removes the eager materialisation + global sort, so
    batches stream out immediately (a partial run now persists data) and memory stays bounded.
    read()/isDirectory() go through the configured driver, so the scan stays remote-storage-safe
    (unlike the native RecursiveDirectoryIterator that commit e994e70 deliberately moved off to fix
    S3/GCS support, issue #32901).

Notes / gotchas:
  * A required ScopeConfigInterface constructor argument is appended (autowired by its magento2-base
    preference). Run setup:di:compile after applying (the composer-patches build recompiles DI
    post-install); a stale compiled DI must be regenerated before the class is instantiated.
  * The set of imported files is now exactly the union of the whitelisted media_gallery_image_folders.
    To keep the derived resize cache (catalog/product/cache/**) out of the media gallery, remove
    catalog/product from media_gallery_image_folders (config) rather than filtering it in this class.
    ResolveNonExistedAssets only deletes rows whose file is physically absent, so existing rows are
    not removed by this change.
  * If media_gallery_image_folders is empty (never the case with shipped config.xml defaults) the
    scan yields nothing rather than the whole tree; this is the safer behaviour and is intentional.

